comment: See [here](https://www.macnconicet.gob.ar/colecciones-2/) for a useful list of collections at the MACN. There appears to be no online database. Important subcodes are MACN-A (Ameghino collection), MACN-Pv (fossil vertebrates), and MACN-Ma (mammals). Within each subcollections, it appears that usually simple increasing numbers were used, but with some exceptions. Sometimes there are two numbers, separated by a space or period, and some of the paleontological numbers are preceded by a code, presumably for the Argentine province (e.g., CH for Chubut).

name: Mongolian Paleontological Center, Geological Institute, Mongolian Academy of Sciences
comment: It appears that there is only a single major repository of paleontological specimens in Ulaanbaatar, but it is cited under a variety of names and it is not clear which one is current. Names encountered include Mongolian Institute of Geology (IGM), Institute of Paleontology and Geology, Mongolian Paleontological Center (MPC), Section of Paleontology and Stratigraphy (PSS or PST) at the Geological Institute (GISPS). Other abbreviations seen include GI and IG. For now I pick "MPC", which appears in relatively recent literature and prominently has an "M" for Mongolia. Most commonly, specimen numbers consist of two numbers separated by a slash (presumably the first is a location or collection number and the second is for an individual specimen), but there are various exceptions, some of which are associated with various joint expeditions.
